[{"id":"VR792789","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a region of space containing a moveable point charge, two possible paths for that point charge, and a fixed point charge. The moveable point charge is on the left side of the figure and path 1 moves horizontally to the right, directly toward the fixed point charge and ends a little over halfway to the fixed point charge. Path 2 curves downward and to the right, then upward and to the right, then upward and to the left and ends at the same point as path 1. The fixed point charge is located to the right of the end of path 1. Throughout its path, Path 2 spirals inward towards the fixed point charge.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR792789.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A region of space contains two positive point charges, one that can be moved around and a second point charge that remains at a fixed position. The figure shows two possible paths, Path <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Path <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, through which the movable point charge can be moved by an external force from an initial position to a final position that is closer to the fixed point charge. Which of the following statements is correct about both the work <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub external\"><math alttext=\"W sub external\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>W</mi><mi>ext</mi></msub></math></span></span> done by the external force and the change <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta U\"><math alttext=\"delta U\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><mi>U</mi></math>